1
00:02:54,883 --> 00:02:57,135
Morning Jose! How are you doing?

2
00:02:57,135 --> 00:02:59,304
Good morning Mr. Abraham! How are you?

3
00:02:59,345 --> 00:03:02,765
I'm good, lose the whole mister thing,

4
00:03:02,807 --> 00:03:04,851
you wouldn't have called me that a month ago.

5
00:03:04,893 --> 00:03:06,978
A month ago you were just Jake.

6
00:03:07,020 --> 00:03:10,940
I still am: save the Mister Abraham for my father.

7
00:03:10,982 --> 00:03:12,483
- Alright --Alright

8
00:03:12,525 --> 00:03:14,485
Hey, we still on for lunch?

9
00:03:14,527 --> 00:03:16,487
Of course, wouldn't miss it for anything!

10
00:03:16,529 --> 00:03:20,033
Okay we'll uh- see you in about an hour.

11
00:03:20,074 --> 00:03:21,326
Sounds good!

12
00:03:28,541 --> 00:03:30,793
[Jose Narrating] I've never seen such a change.

13
00:03:30,835 --> 00:03:32,879
Jake Abraham wasn't always this way

14
00:03:32,921 --> 00:03:37,800
His brother Seth, well... he was born good from his mothers womb

15
00:03:37,842 --> 00:03:42,889
But Jake..
Jake grew up with a chip on his shoulder as bigger as a Sierra Madres

16
00:03:44,766 --> 00:03:47,185
It wasn't that long ago when it blew up.

17
00:03:50,563 --> 00:03:51,981
They're not doing much out there..

18
00:03:52,023 --> 00:03:53,483
Well, we had a glitch-

19
00:03:53,524 --> 00:03:55,860
They're just standing around, it's frustrating!

20
00:03:55,902 --> 00:04:00,198
Just take them some waters, tell them to relax,
we'll get this thing sorted out, okay?

21
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:02,492
Alright.

22
00:04:02,533 --> 00:04:04,619
HAS ANYBODY SEEN JAKE?

23
00:04:17,715 --> 00:04:21,678
Ooh, I would hide if I were you..

24
00:04:21,719 --> 00:04:25,765
.. your brother has been looking for you, he's in one of his moods.

25
00:04:25,807 --> 00:04:30,061
Ah, that's a shock.. I'll be in here.

26
00:04:38,611 --> 00:04:40,071
..shoot.

27
00:05:03,261 --> 00:05:06,264
Jake, you changed the invoicing program.

28
00:05:06,264 --> 00:05:08,474
Yeah, I told you I was going to.

29
00:05:08,516 --> 00:05:11,436
You did it even though I asked you not to.

30
00:05:11,436 --> 00:05:14,605
I know, and now we have a more efficient system.

31
00:05:14,605 --> 00:05:15,857
That's unacceptable.

32
00:05:17,442 --> 00:05:22,530
Okay, what do you want to do, dad, do you want to fire me?

33
00:05:23,781 --> 00:05:28,328
We aren't selling widgets, Jake,
we're selling the best grains and produce in the state..

34
00:05:28,369 --> 00:05:30,955
..and this program you brought in-

35
00:05:30,997 --> 00:05:35,001
The new program is faster than the older one, so what's the problem?

36
00:05:35,043 --> 00:05:37,086
No one knows how to use it..

37
00:05:37,128 --> 00:05:40,798
..so we missed another order this morning
because you haven't properly trained-

38
00:05:40,840 --> 00:05:45,136
Do you expect me to do everything around here?

39
00:05:45,178 --> 00:05:48,973
No.. I just expect you to do your job.

40
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:02,653
Well.. you're up early.

41
00:06:02,653 --> 00:06:05,281
You've got to be kidding me, Mrs. Grey?

42
00:06:05,323 --> 00:06:07,367
Why did you let him in?

43
00:06:07,408 --> 00:06:10,244
What's the matter? Somebody not doing their job?

44
00:06:11,996 --> 00:06:15,666
If you're here to chastise me, dad beat you to it.

45
00:06:15,666 --> 00:06:17,335
You know we didn't get that order in..

46
00:06:17,335 --> 00:06:18,961
I know that.

47
00:06:19,003 --> 00:06:21,547
That means we had guys standing around doing nothing today.

48
00:06:21,589 --> 00:06:23,132
I heard that too..

49
00:06:23,174 --> 00:06:24,717
It costs us money, Jake!

50
00:06:24,759 --> 00:06:26,427
I know.

51
00:06:26,469 --> 00:06:29,055
You know this could have been avoided if
you would have gotten here on time today.

52
00:06:29,097 --> 00:06:33,017
Instead of rolling in late.. hung over.

53
00:06:33,017 --> 00:06:36,396
Great.. anything else?

54
00:06:40,024 --> 00:06:41,526
[mumbles] Pathetic.

55
00:06:53,121 --> 00:06:54,705
I told you to hide.

56
00:06:54,705 --> 00:06:57,917
Why don't you ever knock?

57
00:06:57,959 --> 00:06:59,043
Why should I?

58
00:07:01,254 --> 00:07:04,924
So you don't give me a heart attack, Mrs. Grey, I tend to day dream and

59
00:07:04,966 --> 00:07:09,011
believe it or you're not your not the girl I'm on the beach with.

60
00:07:09,053 --> 00:07:10,721
I like beaches!

61
00:07:12,432 --> 00:07:13,766
Not gonna happen.

62
00:07:13,808 --> 00:07:16,227
Well we've got a problem-

63
00:07:16,269 --> 00:07:21,065
The engine parts for the tractor haven't
arrived and the acreage in the south field is

64
00:07:21,107 --> 00:07:24,694
scheduled for planting when? Tomorrow..

65
00:07:24,735 --> 00:07:30,616
- Okay, um, tell Seth to have the foreman take care off it..

66
00:07:30,658 --> 00:07:33,119
.. delegate some responsibility.

67
00:07:33,161 --> 00:07:36,456
Need I remind you this is something else that could have been avoided

68
00:07:36,497 --> 00:07:39,917
If I had shown up on to work on time, I know..

69
00:07:39,917 --> 00:07:43,254
The rest of us have been here since seven..

70
00:07:46,924 --> 00:07:49,635
Forget it.. call Benward, order the parts.

71
00:07:49,677 --> 00:07:51,387
No, Benward? No!

72
00:07:51,429 --> 00:07:54,557
Yeah, if we go with Benward we can get the engine fixed today.

73
00:07:54,599 --> 00:07:58,102
They use cheap materials, it won't even last one season!

74
00:07:58,144 --> 00:08:04,442
Well, you know,
it's either that or we leave a field full of workers doing nothing all day.

75
00:08:04,442 --> 00:08:05,776
Seth won't like that-

76
00:08:05,776 --> 00:08:08,488
I don't care what Seth thinks, just do it.

77
00:08:10,865 --> 00:08:12,450
Ah, someone's testy...

78
00:08:23,294 --> 00:08:25,463
[Jake] Hey. [Mr Abraham] Hey.

79
00:08:27,298 --> 00:08:30,259
So, have you thought anymore about our conversation yesterday?

80
00:08:30,301 --> 00:08:32,094
Which one?

81
00:08:32,136 --> 00:08:33,971
About the extra vacation week?

82
00:08:34,013 --> 00:08:36,474
Ahh...

83
00:08:36,516 --> 00:08:42,688
I just thought it was only fair,
I've been working in these fields since I was five-

84
00:08:42,730 --> 00:08:47,235
- You're always devising ways to get away from here.. why is that?

85
00:08:49,487 --> 00:08:53,616
It's nothing to do with you dad, I just...

86
00:08:53,658 --> 00:08:56,327
.. this isn't my life.

87
00:08:56,327 --> 00:08:59,038
- Well, what is your life?

88
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:05,711
I don't know.. something more interesting than vegetables.

89
00:09:05,753 --> 00:09:08,714
You know farming is not glamorous.. I give you that.

90
00:09:08,756 --> 00:09:12,343
But it's noble work we do, and it's necessary

91
00:09:12,343 --> 00:09:18,349
Yeah I know,
and I know that it's your dream to have me stay and work on this farm,

92
00:09:18,391 --> 00:09:21,561
but it's not mine.

93
00:09:21,602 --> 00:09:25,982
And for once I would love to be able to go
out and have a good time and not come

94
00:09:26,023 --> 00:09:31,028
back home and expect a sermon, you know?

95
00:09:31,070 --> 00:09:33,990
I'm not expecting you to be perfect, you know?

96
00:09:34,031 --> 00:09:37,201
--I'm so glad you found time to take a break from your busy day.

97
00:09:41,706 --> 00:09:43,416
Oops..

98
00:09:43,457 --> 00:09:45,835
You're coming with me today to talk to the customers.

99
00:09:45,876 --> 00:09:47,169
Why?

100
00:09:47,211 --> 00:09:49,672
Because they're going to be mad, and I'm tired of covering for you.

101
00:09:49,714 --> 00:09:53,217
Oh, well I don't deal with customers, so too bad.

102
00:09:53,217 --> 00:09:55,553
Then what is it that you DO here?

103
00:09:55,595 --> 00:09:58,180
You know what Seth? I wouldn't expect you to

104
00:09:58,222 --> 00:10:00,850
understand what I do, especially since you never

105
00:10:00,891 --> 00:10:03,227
Never what?

106
00:10:03,269 --> 00:10:04,729
.. Nothing.

107
00:10:04,729 --> 00:10:06,564
No, come on, PLEASE say it.

108
00:10:06,606 --> 00:10:10,276
Huh? Never what? Never went to college?
No, I had to stay here and work.

109
00:10:10,318 --> 00:10:14,572
I didn't have the luxury of wasting time
hanging out at parties and skipping classes

110
00:10:14,614 --> 00:10:15,740
Calm down..

111
00:10:15,740 --> 00:10:17,783
No, you're right, hey Seth, THANK YOU!

112
00:10:17,825 --> 00:10:21,954
Thank you SO MUCH for sticking around,
because we all know how hard it is to find

113
00:10:21,996 --> 00:10:23,914
someone who can drive a TRACTOR.

114
00:10:24,415 --> 00:10:25,249
[Mr Abraham] SETH!

115
00:10:25,249 --> 00:10:26,917
You're a disgrace to this family!

116
00:10:26,917 --> 00:10:28,753
Admit it, you're jealous! -Yeah!?

117
00:10:28,753 --> 00:10:30,921
Yeah, you always have been!

118
00:10:30,921 --> 00:10:33,591
- Is that it?!? COME ON! SHOW ME HOW JEALOUS I AM!
- SAY IT! I WANT YOU TO SAY IT!

119
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:34,675
STOP!

120
00:10:42,266 --> 00:10:43,851
.. Just go..

121
00:10:44,935 --> 00:10:47,438
..What are you waiting for? Just leave!

122
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:50,816
Make our lives easier and just get out!

123
00:11:08,626 --> 00:11:12,797
I'm sorry Seth, I didn't know that was yours..

124
00:11:12,838 --> 00:11:14,674
.. Don't worry about it.

125
00:11:24,975 --> 00:11:27,478
You okay?

126
00:11:27,478 --> 00:11:30,356
Yeah, I'm fine..

127
00:11:30,398 --> 00:11:33,317
I switched back to the old invoicing program.

128
00:11:38,823 --> 00:11:42,702
You know Seth, got that hot temper..

129
00:11:42,743 --> 00:11:44,495
Yeah..

130
00:11:44,537 --> 00:11:46,664
You know, he's got a point though..

131
00:11:48,999 --> 00:11:52,503
..I don't know what I'm still doing here.

132
00:11:54,422 --> 00:11:57,007
What do you mean?

133
00:11:57,007 --> 00:11:58,843
I mean I want to leave.

134
00:12:02,930 --> 00:12:04,181
You can't just do that..

135
00:12:04,223 --> 00:12:09,520
Yeah, I can, and I want to, I mean, I...

136
00:12:09,562 --> 00:12:13,357
I need to live my life and I'm not doing that here..

137
00:12:16,193 --> 00:12:18,070
I quit, dad..

138
00:12:20,364 --> 00:12:25,369
..and since I'm quitting,
maybe we should talk about a severance package.

139
00:12:28,914 --> 00:12:31,542
It usually doesn't work that way..

140
00:12:31,584 --> 00:12:36,464
Well, then I need some money to get started.. make some investments.

141
00:12:38,799 --> 00:12:40,885
How much are you asking for?

142
00:12:43,554 --> 00:12:46,056
What about my inheritance?

143
00:12:46,056 --> 00:12:50,561
I take that now and I could double it or
more by the time I would have received it.

144
00:12:53,939 --> 00:12:55,316
.. I'd have to think on it.

145
00:12:58,235 --> 00:12:59,236
Okay..

146
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:06,035
.. Think about it and let me know.

147
00:13:06,076 --> 00:13:11,582
Cause either way, I'm gone as soon as I get my stuff together.

148
00:13:38,192 --> 00:13:40,778
Mrs. Grey..

149
00:13:40,820 --> 00:13:44,448
.. Would you get Mr. Ferris on the phone for me?

150
00:13:44,448 --> 00:13:46,116
I'll take it in my office.

151
00:13:46,784 --> 00:13:49,453
Sure.. will do.

152
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:03,425
So how's Seth doing? How are his roses?

153
00:14:03,467 --> 00:14:05,845
The garden is beautiful.

154
00:14:05,886 --> 00:14:08,347
- Hey Mr Ferris.

155
00:14:08,389 --> 00:14:09,974
Jake! Haven't seen you in a long time.

156
00:14:10,015 --> 00:14:11,976
Yeah, it's been a while

157
00:14:12,017 --> 00:14:15,813
So, uh.. so how's this all work?

158
00:14:15,813 --> 00:14:18,440
Well, there's a few steps we have to take..

159
00:14:18,482 --> 00:14:20,317
.. Well how many steps can there be?

160
00:14:25,489 --> 00:14:29,285
Down at the bottom of the page here is what
your going to be receiving as your share

161
00:14:29,326 --> 00:14:32,204
of the inheritance, you're going get it all in one check,

162
00:14:32,246 --> 00:14:35,416
but there is some paper work we have to do to finalize all of this.

163
00:14:36,417 --> 00:14:38,836
Well, are you sure you want to do this?

164
00:14:38,878 --> 00:14:42,339
Yes, yeah, I told you I was.

165
00:14:42,339 --> 00:14:47,303
Okay, I'm your father, you know? I love you,
I want to make sure you're alright.

166
00:14:47,344 --> 00:14:52,641
I'm fine, okay? I'm an adult, I can take care of myself.

167
00:14:52,683 --> 00:14:54,268
Alright.

168
00:14:56,520 --> 00:14:59,315
Mr. Ferris, go ahead and draw up the papers.

169
00:14:59,356 --> 00:15:00,774
They'll be ready first thing in the morning.

170
00:15:12,369 --> 00:15:14,872
There you go. -Thank you, Jake.

171
00:15:14,914 --> 00:15:17,291
And this is for you.

172
00:15:19,710 --> 00:15:22,296
Thank you, thank you so much.

173
00:15:28,761 --> 00:15:30,554
A fool and his money..

174
00:15:38,771 --> 00:15:40,564
Do you know where you're going to live?

175
00:15:43,776 --> 00:15:46,570
Not yet.. I'll figure it out.

176
00:15:49,073 --> 00:15:51,742
Here.. take this.

177
00:15:54,244 --> 00:15:55,913
.. This is grandpa's watch.

178
00:15:55,955 --> 00:15:58,749
Yeah.. I want you to have it.

179
00:16:01,585 --> 00:16:03,253
Does it even work?

180
00:16:03,253 --> 00:16:05,089
Yeah, it works well.

181
00:16:05,130 --> 00:16:07,508
But um, mostly just uh..

182
00:16:10,928 --> 00:16:14,098
.. just take it.. I want you to have it.

183
00:16:18,519 --> 00:16:19,436
Thanks.

184
00:16:21,438 --> 00:16:24,608
A lot of people are going to miss you, Jake..

185
00:16:24,608 --> 00:16:30,656
A lot of people? Come on dad.. it's better for everyone that I'm going.

186
00:16:30,698 --> 00:16:32,616
You're not doing this for us.

187
00:16:34,952 --> 00:16:36,161
No, you're right.

188
00:16:38,998 --> 00:16:43,502
I should.. I should get going.

189
00:16:43,544 --> 00:16:45,587
Take care buddy.

190
00:16:45,629 --> 00:16:46,964
Thank you.

191
00:16:47,006 --> 00:16:48,632
Alright, drive careful.

192
00:17:13,490 --> 00:17:16,368
[Radio DJ 1] I'm Andy Greenberg,
and I'm going to change the way you think.

193
00:17:16,410 --> 00:17:20,956
You know how often you have read,
and people have told you, "Believe In Yourself"

194
00:17:20,998 --> 00:17:23,667
That's right, you tell it to people, people tell it to you,

195
00:17:23,667 --> 00:17:26,712
But you know what? That's absolutely WRONG, I-

196
00:17:26,754 --> 00:17:30,632
[Radio DJ 2] -It used to be that a man's word was his bond;
but in the city?

197
00:17:30,674 --> 00:17:33,969
I mean, it's still that way in the rural areas, but in the cities?

198
00:17:34,011 --> 00:17:36,013
You better watch out for the sharks!

199
00:17:36,013 --> 00:17:40,476
[Radio DJ 3] As I was saying,
don't let women beguile you; some women use men,

200
00:17:40,517 --> 00:17:43,854
In other words, they can out use their abusers.

201
00:17:43,896 --> 00:17:46,356
[Radio DJ 4] Because if you're obsessed with what someone else has,

202
00:17:46,356 --> 00:17:50,360
instead of with what you have,
you'll never be happy, you'll never be at peace.

203
00:17:52,905 --> 00:17:55,741
We all want to connect with other people,
but the great thing about family connections

204
00:17:55,783 --> 00:17:59,578
is they are utterly indestructible, you can't take away the-

205
00:17:59,620 --> 00:18:09,713
[Radio Music]

206
00:20:19,676 --> 00:20:20,552
We've only got in the one..

207
00:20:22,554 --> 00:20:23,889
Yeah, I'll take it.

208
00:20:23,931 --> 00:20:27,351
Excellent! But.. will it go with your new sports car?

209
00:20:28,560 --> 00:20:30,479
Which is your favorite out of these here?

210
00:20:30,520 --> 00:20:31,730
- My favorite? - Yeah.

211
00:20:35,192 --> 00:20:38,028
This piece here, it's stunning.

212
00:20:38,070 --> 00:20:40,030
If I could, I'd get it for myself.

213
00:20:42,032 --> 00:20:42,783
It is beautiful..

214
00:20:45,702 --> 00:20:47,162
I'll take that as well.

215
00:20:47,204 --> 00:20:50,040
Is it for your wife, or.. girlfriend?

216
00:20:50,082 --> 00:20:51,333
It's for you.

217
00:20:51,375 --> 00:20:52,376
For me?

218
00:20:52,417 --> 00:20:53,418
Yeah, for you.

219
00:20:53,460 --> 00:20:54,044
You're joking!

220
00:20:54,086 --> 00:20:55,254
No.

221
00:20:55,295 --> 00:20:56,713
You look like you deserve it..

222
00:20:56,713 --> 00:20:59,258
Oh my gosh..

223
00:22:33,477 --> 00:22:34,644
Who is she?

224
00:22:34,686 --> 00:22:37,147
Oh that's Laura.. she's an actress also.

225
00:22:37,147 --> 00:22:38,648
Really?

226
00:22:38,690 --> 00:22:42,069
We recently worked together on a film called "A Box for Rob".

227
00:22:59,336 --> 00:23:01,838
And this is Frank.

228
00:23:01,838 --> 00:23:03,632
Good evening.

229
00:23:03,673 --> 00:23:05,884
Frank owns the place, Frank, this is Jake.

230
00:23:05,926 --> 00:23:07,344
Hi, Jake.

231
00:23:07,386 --> 00:23:09,679
- Hey, nice to meet you. -Yeah, pleasure.

232
00:23:09,721 --> 00:23:11,848
- So are you enjoying yourself? -We are.

233
00:23:11,848 --> 00:23:13,433
Well, you should be, you have lovely company.

234
00:23:15,268 --> 00:23:16,186
If I can get you anything, let me know.

235
00:23:16,186 --> 00:23:18,313
Ok, will do.

236
00:23:18,355 --> 00:23:21,358
Arial, comp this table.

237
00:23:25,362 --> 00:23:27,614
So, an actress, huh?

238
00:23:30,534 --> 00:23:32,536
You really like her.

239
00:23:32,577 --> 00:23:34,579
Yes, it's obvious.

240
00:23:36,373 --> 00:23:38,667
Cheers ladies-

241
00:23:38,708 --> 00:23:41,169
- to a great night.

242
00:23:41,211 --> 00:23:43,213
Drink up, we need another bottle.

243
00:24:00,730 --> 00:24:02,607
Can I buy you a drink?

244
00:24:02,649 --> 00:24:03,900
Do I know you?

245
00:24:03,900 --> 00:24:07,028
Not yet.. I'm Jake.

246
00:24:07,070 --> 00:24:07,904
Laura.

247
00:24:09,656 --> 00:24:11,116
Are you new to the city?

248
00:24:11,158 --> 00:24:13,785
Just moved, actually..

249
00:24:13,827 --> 00:24:15,745
What do you do?

250
00:24:15,787 --> 00:24:17,456
I do lots of things.

251
00:24:17,497 --> 00:24:22,043
Okay, well.. how about your job?

252
00:24:22,085 --> 00:24:25,422
Okay.. I'm an investor.

253
00:24:26,590 --> 00:24:28,300
Stock market?

