01:06:53,718 --> 01:06:55,261
So?

762
01:06:55,302 --> 01:06:59,140
So the assets, the stocks.. everything is frozen by the SCC

763
01:06:59,181 --> 01:07:03,102
which means you and I now own shares that mean nothing.

764
01:07:03,144 --> 01:07:09,608
We can't do anything with it, we can't share them,
we can't trade then, we can't sell them.

765
01:07:09,650 --> 01:07:15,990
They're stuck.. ok? They're stuck,
just sitting there in the account, doing nothing.

766
01:07:17,199 --> 01:07:19,660
It'll take a lawsuit to get our money back..

767
01:07:19,702 --> 01:07:21,829
How long's it going to take?

768
01:07:21,871 --> 01:07:25,791
Months? Years, even, who knows? Even then,
we'll only get pennies back on the dollar.

769
01:07:25,833 --> 01:07:26,959
No..

770
01:07:27,001 --> 01:07:29,170
- Yeah, we're toast. - No, YOU'RE toast!

771
01:07:29,170 --> 01:07:31,672
Frank made the investment on YOUR recommendation.

772
01:07:31,672 --> 01:07:33,799
Yeah, well, he KNEW it was a risk he cant hold that against me

773
01:07:33,841 --> 01:07:37,303
Do you understand what an IDIOT you've
made me look like in front of all my friends

774
01:07:37,344 --> 01:07:40,848
saying that "we're going forward with this movie project"?
You're disgusting..

775
01:07:40,848 --> 01:07:44,810
Alright, settle down, okay? All we have to do is think of a new plan..

776
01:07:44,852 --> 01:07:48,064
No, no, no, I don't know if you've noticed, but there's no more "we"..

777
01:08:58,676 --> 01:09:06,475
[Phone Ringing]

778
01:09:06,517 --> 01:09:07,935
.. Hi.

779
01:09:07,935 --> 01:09:11,105
Look, I know your mad at me, but have you seen Frank?

780
01:09:11,147 --> 01:09:16,986
Yeah.. um.. he thinks you lied about everything.

781
01:09:17,027 --> 01:09:19,446
- I didn't. - Doesn't matter.

782
01:09:19,488 --> 01:09:24,493
He's out half a million dollars because of you..
he's coming for his money.

783
01:09:24,535 --> 01:09:26,245
I don't have it!

784
01:09:26,287 --> 01:09:31,125
He's not going to stop until he finds you, Jake.. he'll kill you.

785
01:09:31,125 --> 01:09:35,963
Okay, okay, fine tell him.. look, tell him he can have the condo, alright?

786
01:09:35,963 --> 01:09:37,965
The car.. I-I'll leave the keys for him.

787
01:09:38,007 --> 01:09:39,592
Jake, that's not going to work..

788
01:09:39,633 --> 01:09:43,470
Frank isn't exactly the kind of person to hold a garage sale..

789
01:09:43,470 --> 01:09:45,139
.. You're gonna have to come up with the cash.

790
01:09:45,139 --> 01:09:47,474
I lost WAY more than he did!

791
01:09:47,516 --> 01:09:48,184
He doesn't care..

792
01:09:51,478 --> 01:09:53,981
I can't pay him, okay?

793
01:09:55,232 --> 01:09:57,902
Then you better disappear.

794
01:10:50,246 --> 01:10:51,538
[Knocking]

795
01:10:54,250 --> 01:10:56,085
[Knocking]

796
01:10:57,211 --> 01:10:58,712
May I help you?

797
01:10:58,754 --> 01:11:00,047
Yeah, I need to talk to Jake.

798
01:11:00,089 --> 01:11:02,549
Jake is not here right now.

799
01:11:02,549 --> 01:11:03,509
You know when he'll be back?

800
01:11:03,550 --> 01:11:05,261
I have no idea..

801
01:11:05,302 --> 01:11:06,887
You have any idea where he might be?

802
01:11:06,929 --> 01:11:08,889
No, he didn't let me know where he was going.

803
01:11:10,975 --> 01:11:13,310
Jake? JAKE!

804
01:12:40,481 --> 01:12:41,648
Here you go, sir.

805
01:12:41,690 --> 01:12:42,483
Thank you, have a good one.

806
01:12:43,984 --> 01:12:46,320
Hi, uh.. Number 6, please.

807
01:12:53,202 --> 01:12:54,328
It's not going through, sir.

808
01:12:58,165 --> 01:12:59,917
It's a new card, try that..

809
01:13:02,544 --> 01:13:03,837
Im sorry, sir..

810
01:13:06,256 --> 01:13:09,176
Uh.. that.

811
01:13:12,012 --> 01:13:13,514
That one doesn't work either, sir.

812
01:13:15,349 --> 01:13:17,768
Alright, thanks..

813
01:14:06,233 --> 01:14:11,071
Hey.. hey, it's me, um..

814
01:14:11,113 --> 01:14:13,907
Look, I need your help..

815
01:14:13,907 --> 01:14:14,825
What?

816
01:14:16,076 --> 01:14:17,661
Your boyfriend's still after me..

817
01:14:21,498 --> 01:14:26,962
No, you're not listening, I need.. I just need a place to crash!

818
01:14:27,004 --> 01:14:31,925
Anywhere! I don't care! Friends, relatives, someone you don't know,

819
01:14:31,967 --> 01:14:37,097
Just, I need.. I need ANYTHING! Anything will help, please!

820
01:14:39,141 --> 01:14:41,435
Tell me where you are, I'll come and get you.

821
01:14:48,775 --> 01:14:50,652
Where is he?

822
01:14:50,694 --> 01:14:51,945
Bridge on Hawthorne..

823
01:14:55,449 --> 01:14:59,036
Tank? Meet me in about five minutes..

824
01:15:10,797 --> 01:15:11,298
Laura?

825
01:15:14,134 --> 01:15:16,178
Look, Frank..

826
01:15:16,220 --> 01:15:18,347
Frank, these things happen, okay? It's not my

827
01:15:21,308 --> 01:15:26,647
You make me chase you all over town?
You make me chase you like I'm some chump?!?

828
01:15:26,647 --> 01:15:29,149
Have my car, my condo, it's yours, ok?

829
01:15:29,149 --> 01:15:30,651
I want my money, you understand?

830
01:15:32,819 --> 01:15:36,698
I want my MONEY! THAT'S what I want!

831
01:15:36,740 --> 01:15:38,659
TAKE ACCOUNTABILITY!

832
01:15:40,661 --> 01:15:43,413
You've got a week! Tell 'im!

833
01:16:30,711 --> 01:16:32,879
What happened to you?

834
01:16:32,879 --> 01:16:34,673
Long story..

835
01:16:34,715 --> 01:16:36,550
Usually is..

836
01:16:36,592 --> 01:16:38,719
I need a gun.

837
01:16:38,719 --> 01:16:39,970
Have you ever used one?

838
01:16:41,555 --> 01:16:42,931
No.

839
01:16:42,973 --> 01:16:45,475
You've gotta get training to be able to use it safely.

840
01:16:51,732 --> 01:16:55,068
Here.. can I trade this for one?

841
01:16:55,110 --> 01:16:58,196
We don't do trades here.. we aren't a pawn shop.

842
01:16:58,238 --> 01:17:00,741
I don't have money.

843
01:17:00,741 --> 01:17:05,245
Well, I can't do it.. that looks like a special watch.. you ought-a keep it.

844
01:19:06,074 --> 01:19:08,243
Hey.

845
01:19:08,285 --> 01:19:10,912
Names Al.

846
01:19:10,954 --> 01:19:13,999
Jake.

847
01:19:14,040 --> 01:19:18,211
Hungry?

848
01:19:18,253 --> 01:19:19,296
Apparently.

849
01:19:22,215 --> 01:19:26,553
First piece of advice..
your sob story is not any better than anybody else's in here,

850
01:19:26,595 --> 01:19:28,263
so don't think you'll win any sympathy.

851
01:19:30,223 --> 01:19:32,893
I never said that..

852
01:19:35,061 --> 01:19:37,564
Where do they get the food from anyway?

853
01:19:37,606 --> 01:19:43,028
People fulfill the needs of other
anonymously through "My Neighbor in Need"

854
01:19:43,069 --> 01:19:45,739
Yeah, I saw that on the way in.

855
01:19:45,781 --> 01:19:50,160
It's true; strangers are helping strangers everyday.

856
01:19:52,120 --> 01:19:56,833
Let me guess: you were on top of the world.. rich and popular.

857
01:20:00,420 --> 01:20:02,047
College degree?

858
01:20:02,088 --> 01:20:04,090
Yep.

859
01:20:04,090 --> 01:20:07,469
Well, how 'bout that? We've got ourselves a speller!

860
01:20:07,511 --> 01:20:10,931
Maybe you could help some of the boys with their signs.

861
01:20:12,516 --> 01:20:15,435
Number two: Don't pan-handle at the gray house down the street.

862
01:20:15,477 --> 01:20:18,772
They're Canadians; takes forever to get rid of those quarters.

863
01:20:20,273 --> 01:20:22,067
Okay?

864
01:20:22,108 --> 01:20:24,986
Three: You need to have prepared answers for the two

865
01:20:25,028 --> 01:20:27,280
most common questions you'll get in here.

866
01:20:27,864 --> 01:20:29,241
Yeah? What's that?

867
01:20:29,282 --> 01:20:30,116
"Why are you homeless?"

868
01:20:31,117 --> 01:20:34,120
I always answer "by choice".

869
01:20:35,789 --> 01:20:39,125
It takes them a while to come up with a follow up.

870
01:20:39,167 --> 01:20:41,127
And the second question?

871
01:20:43,004 --> 01:20:48,802
Well, this place is run by a church,
so they'll wanna know if you need prayer.

872
01:20:50,178 --> 01:20:52,472
What do you say?

873
01:20:52,472 --> 01:20:55,976
I always say "yes"..

874
01:20:55,976 --> 01:20:58,478
.. but you'll need to come up with your own answer.

875
01:20:59,688 --> 01:21:03,984
Practice: Do you need to pray with someone?

876
01:21:05,819 --> 01:21:07,863
I'm fine.

877
01:21:10,991 --> 01:21:14,661
Yeah.. I don't think you'll get away with that answer..

878
01:21:14,661 --> 01:21:15,829
Why not?

879
01:21:15,871 --> 01:21:17,038
'Cause you're lying.

880
01:21:21,668 --> 01:21:23,670
I'm going to get some food.

881
01:21:31,094 --> 01:21:34,264
You'd think after fourteen hours of work I could get some sleep.

882
01:21:35,223 --> 01:21:37,100
You have a job?

883
01:21:41,021 --> 01:21:43,273
I'm homeless, not jobless.

884
01:21:48,194 --> 01:21:50,280
Where do you work?

885
01:21:50,739 --> 01:21:51,239
On a farm.

886
01:21:52,616 --> 01:21:53,700
Really?

887
01:21:55,869 --> 01:22:03,043
Yeah, it's a pig farm.. nothing glamorous, but it pays the bills.

888
01:22:04,544 --> 01:22:06,212
I use to work on a farm.

889
01:22:09,799 --> 01:22:11,384
You don't look it.

890
01:22:11,426 --> 01:22:16,723
Yeah.. yeah that's cause I gave it up.

891
01:22:16,765 --> 01:22:20,393
Of course you did.

892
01:22:20,435 --> 01:22:23,605
For all of this..

893
01:22:25,732 --> 01:22:28,568
There may be some work on the farm if you decide to get back into it.

894
01:22:28,610 --> 01:22:33,990
No, no way.. I am DONE with farm life..

895
01:22:37,577 --> 01:22:42,666
It's the Dickenson Farm north on 17.. if you change your mind.

896
01:22:45,001 --> 01:22:48,672
Thanks, but.. I'm good.

897
01:24:35,403 --> 01:24:37,363
Jake!

898
01:24:37,363 --> 01:24:38,907
Is that you?

899
01:24:38,948 --> 01:24:40,075
Hey!

900
01:24:43,578 --> 01:24:45,538
- Hey, Al.. - You came!

901
01:24:45,580 --> 01:24:48,708
Yeah.. yeah, I came..

902
01:24:48,708 --> 01:24:52,253
Did you come to work? Because we've got plenty of work.

903
01:24:54,380 --> 01:24:56,716
Yeah, actually, that'd be great.

904
01:24:56,758 --> 01:24:59,761
Good, good..

905
01:24:59,803 --> 01:25:02,222
Sorry, can I look at that?

906
01:25:02,222 --> 01:25:03,389
- This? - Yeah.

907
01:25:10,939 --> 01:25:12,982
Come on kid, lets go to work.

908
01:25:14,067 --> 01:25:15,443
Yeah, okay.

909
01:25:23,827 --> 01:25:25,078
You know, it's hard to believe..

910
01:25:25,078 --> 01:25:26,871
What's that?

911
01:25:26,913 --> 01:25:30,250
Well, not that long ago, I was buying a speaker system for my condo..

912
01:25:30,291 --> 01:25:30,959
Yeah?

913
01:25:31,000 --> 01:25:33,086
Yeah, surround sound..

914
01:25:33,086 --> 01:25:34,754
Was it any good?

915
01:25:34,754 --> 01:25:36,881
I don't know.. I never got to use it.

916
01:25:36,923 --> 01:25:39,008
- Too bad. - Yeah.

917
01:25:41,344 --> 01:25:45,598
You know the fall from the top is a LOT shorter than you might think?

918
01:25:45,598 --> 01:25:49,894
- No one ever tells you that either - Jake.. it's real simple.

919
01:25:49,936 --> 01:25:50,770
What is?

920
01:25:50,770 --> 01:25:53,565
You have a home.. go back to it.

921
01:25:53,606 --> 01:25:57,652
No, no, I can't go back to the farm..

922
01:25:57,694 --> 01:25:58,820
Why not?

923
01:25:58,862 --> 01:26:00,947
Because, they wouldn't take me

924
01:26:00,989 --> 01:26:02,740
They're your family.

925
01:26:02,782 --> 01:26:06,661
No, you don't understand, I abandoned them, okay? I betrayed them..

926
01:26:08,371 --> 01:26:10,957
Well you have a choice: you can stay here with the pigs,

927
01:26:10,999 --> 01:26:13,334
or you can go back home with the people that truly love you.

928
01:26:13,376 --> 01:26:15,336
How do you know they love me?

929
01:26:15,378 --> 01:26:18,006
Well earlier you said your father is a man of faith, right?

930
01:26:18,047 --> 01:26:19,924
Yeah?

931
01:26:19,966 --> 01:26:22,468
If that's true, then he understands a love that's greater than all sin.

932
01:26:30,018 --> 01:26:32,812
You know, I have a friend who predicted this..

933
01:26:32,854 --> 01:26:34,439
What's that?

934
01:26:34,480 --> 01:26:38,318
Just that I would come face to face with myself.. with God..

935
01:26:41,905 --> 01:26:43,323
.. I don't know..

936
01:26:44,657 --> 01:26:48,786
.. maybe I could earn their love back, you know?

937
01:26:48,828 --> 01:26:53,458
Go back, work on the farm for no pay, just for food.

938
01:26:53,499 --> 01:26:56,711
Hey.. whatever gets you out of this pig pen.

939
01:27:00,340 --> 01:27:04,844
Oh, this is going to be a LOT more painful than losing all my stuff,
I'll tell you that.

940
01:27:06,179 --> 01:27:09,766
Well, I wouldn't know.. I never had surround sound.

941
01:27:12,852 --> 01:27:14,187
Thanks Al.

942
01:27:14,187 --> 01:27:15,939
Yeah, sure thing kid.

943
01:28:46,112 --> 01:28:49,574
I need you to call these guys makes sure
they are still on board with us, okay?

944
01:28:49,615 --> 01:28:52,410
Well, do you want me to email them the new numbers too?

945
01:28:52,452 --> 01:28:55,496
Absolutely, they have to know that we're still viable, okay?

946
01:28:55,538 --> 01:28:57,582
My dad has some new numbers.

947
01:28:57,623 --> 01:29:00,293
Dad, do you have the new numbers we can give to the vendors?

948
01:29:01,669 --> 01:29:02,962
.. Dad?

949
01:29:09,344 --> 01:29:10,970
Dad?

950
01:29:41,167 --> 01:29:44,087
I messed up, dad, I lost it..

951
01:29:46,005 --> 01:29:47,965
.. I lost everything.

952
01:29:48,007 --> 01:29:53,346
No, you didn't lose us.. you didn't lose me.

953
01:29:53,388 --> 01:29:57,683
You're my son.. you'll always be that.

954
01:30:03,272 --> 01:30:05,066
I'm so glad you're home...

955
01:30:11,697 --> 01:30:13,241
.. I'm so glad you're home.

956
01:30:20,957 --> 01:30:22,333
Dad..

957
01:30:22,375 --> 01:30:24,210
So, uh.

958
01:30:24,210 --> 01:30:28,881
.. so what's going on? I read an article that the farm was closing down..

959
01:30:28,923 --> 01:30:35,012
Our church gave us everything we needed.. our Father provided.

960
01:30:35,054 --> 01:30:40,059
All our prayers were answered.. all of our prayers!

961
01:30:47,400 --> 01:30:50,278
Hey everybody! Look who's here!

962
01:30:55,074 --> 01:31:04,083
[All cheering]

963
01:31:04,125 --> 01:31:06,669
It's time for a celebration!

964
01:31:09,755 --> 01:31:12,133
You never gave up on me, dad..

965
01:31:12,175 --> 01:31:13,468
Never.

966
01:31:32,320 --> 01:31:33,863
Hey, Jake?

967
01:31:38,493 --> 01:31:40,828
I got these for you.

968
01:31:41,621 --> 01:31:42,955
Where did you get these?

969
01:31:42,997 --> 01:31:46,667
I got those before you left.

970
01:31:46,709 --> 01:31:48,836
.. and the clothes?

971
01:31:48,878 --> 01:31:51,964
The clothes I got for you.. just in case.

972
01:31:55,134 --> 01:31:57,303
And I got this ring I want you to have..

973
01:32:03,851 --> 01:32:09,315
Look, dad, I don't deserve any of this

974
01:32:09,315 --> 01:32:10,191
Hey.

975
01:32:13,069 --> 01:32:16,030
You don't have to do anything to deserve it.

976
01:32:18,324 --> 01:32:19,867
I love you.

977
01:32:45,768 --> 01:32:48,020
You're throwing him a PARTY?

978
01:32:50,356 --> 01:32:53,859
Well.. your brother has returned..

979
01:32:55,945 --> 01:32:59,699
All these years I've worked for you, I followed your guidance,

980
01:32:59,740 --> 01:33:02,535
I've done everything that you've asked of me..

981
01:33:02,577 --> 01:33:05,204
.. you never celebrated me like that.

982
01:33:06,205 --> 01:33:08,082
Seth..

983
01:33:08,124 --> 01:33:14,839
..I have withheld NOTHING from you.. everything I have is yours.

984
01:33:14,880 --> 01:33:21,762
Jake comes crawling back here,
after wasting everything on who knows what,

985
01:33:21,804 --> 01:33:23,723
and you want to celebrate that?

986
01:33:26,475 --> 01:33:31,897
We're all together again..
and we are celebrating your brothers return home

987
01:33:31,939 --> 01:33:35,901
because he was dead, and now he is alive..

988
01:33:38,404 --> 01:33:40,990
.. he was lost, now he is found.

989
01:33:59,133 --> 01:34:05,890
Right on top, right on top the hotdog, thanks Ms. Grey.

990
01:34:05,931 --> 01:34:07,266
I'm so glad to have you home, honey.

991
01:34:12,647 --> 01:34:14,649
Hey, good to see you.

992
01:34:18,361 --> 01:34:20,279
Good to see you guys.

993
01:34:24,992 --> 01:34:29,455
Oh ok, I see how it is.. you did it, dad!

994
01:34:29,455 --> 01:34:31,165
I mean, we haven't had a party like this since

995
01:34:31,207 --> 01:34:33,209
Since the day you left.

996
01:34:35,961 --> 01:34:38,339
Alright, wow, a sense of humor!

997
01:34:38,381 --> 01:34:41,300
Yeah, yeah.. I found it the other day, you like it?

998
01:34:41,342 --> 01:34:42,968
I'll have to get used to it..

999
01:34:44,512 --> 01:34:49,850
So dad, I was thinking.. I know what I want to do for the farm.

1000
01:34:49,892 --> 01:34:52,812
My two sons, I love you.

1001
01:34:52,812 --> 01:34:54,313
We love you too, dad.

1002
01:34:59,485 --> 01:35:01,195
I heard you served coffee in here.

1003
01:35:04,532 --> 01:35:07,868
Wow, looks like you got yourself a proper job.

1004
01:35:07,910 --> 01:35:13,499
Yeah.. told my father I wanted to learn
the company from the ground up, so..

1005
01:35:13,499 --> 01:35:15,209
You went home?

1006
01:35:15,251 --> 01:35:17,336
Yeah, I did..

1007
01:35:18,170 --> 01:35:20,506
That's good.. good for you.

1008
01:35:24,844 --> 01:35:26,887
I was a jerk, Summer.

1009
01:35:31,016 --> 01:35:33,060
- .. yeah. - Yeah.

1010
01:35:34,854 --> 01:35:38,524
And, um.. I'm sorry.

1011
01:35:40,192 --> 01:35:42,069
I really am..

1012
01:35:43,779 --> 01:35:45,197
.. Do you forgive me?

1013
01:35:52,204 --> 01:35:53,539
Yeah.

1014
01:35:55,374 --> 01:35:56,625
Yeah?

1015
01:35:58,711 --> 01:36:03,132
Um.. you think maybe we could just start over?

1016
01:36:05,551 --> 01:36:07,887
Start what over?

1017
01:36:07,887 --> 01:36:14,810
Well, I make deliveries on Wednesdays now,
so maybe next week I can take you to dinner..

1018
01:36:16,479 --> 01:36:18,230
What do you say?

1019
01:36:18,272 --> 01:36:23,486
Well, um.. something expensive?

1020
01:36:25,571 --> 01:36:29,575
